    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor: The reason Enid Nemy and others cited in her essay "The Mementos That Got Away" (Aug. 2) didn't buy a pricey souvenir at a distant vacation spot is because so many "objets d'art" are schlocky and/or rip-offs. Common sense prevails. Would I buy this in Bloomingdale's? So many souvenirs that can't be recycled as gifts as the author suggests end up in garage sales or in the mother of all garage sales, Goodwill thrift shops.  JOAN MARY MACEY Binghamton, N.Y.</p>
      </block>
